title: Qld premier says budget will help woes
text:
Thu, Sep 3, 2015, 4:30 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Qld premier says budget will help woes AAP – 1 hour 14 minutes ago Recommend Print 
Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk has reassured Queenslanders her budget will help the state get back on track after another round of disappointing economic figures. 
Australian Bureau of Statistics figures released on Wednesday showed final demand for Queensland fell 0.8 per cent in the June quarter, rounding off a year of negative final demand figures in the state. 
"These figures are actually better then they were last year and I know our budget is measured, it's responsible," Ms Palaszczuk told reporters in Townsville. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Myer shares hit all-time low AAP
